owl:Ontology.terms:abstract: FoodleMaps provides a way to create restaurant entities, with a detailed description of dishes in the menu. Dishes can be characterized by the used ingredients, but also by the preparation time, by some characteristic and others. This makes the ontology useful to design an application to help users in finding restaurants according to their needs.
owl:Ontology.terms:creator: https://alexmv12.xyz/
https://github.com/FrancescoAttorre
owl:Ontology.terms:description: FoodleMaps is a an ontology designed to support an application which lets users find restaurant serving dishes with constraints on ingredients, diet, etc.
owl:Ontology.schema:name: FoodleMaps
owl:Ontology.rdfs:label: FoodleMaps

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasMenu

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates a dietary restriction or guideline for which this recipe or menu item is suitable, e.g. diabetic, halal etc.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: suitableForDiet

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Assigns one characteristic to a dish.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasCharacteristic

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Associates an ingredient to a recipe.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasIngredient

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Associates a Recipe to a MenuItem.MenuItems can have multiple recipes, to indicate different versions of the same dish.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasRecipe

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Used to express a constraint wanted by the user to a specific characteristic.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: requiresCharacteristic

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Used to express a diet followed by the user; the returned dishes will have to be suitable for that diet.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: requiresDiet

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Connects a Menu to some Recipes, served by that menu.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: servesRecipe

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates how many minutes are needed to prepare and serve the dish. More precisely, is the time which should pass between the moment in which the order is made and the moment in which the dish is server.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hasPreparationTime

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Food is any eatable or drinkable substance that is normally consumed by humans.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Food

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A structured representation of food or drink items available from a FoodEstablishment.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Menu

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A food or drink item listed in a menu or menu section.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: MenuItem

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A recipe. For dietary restrictions covered by the recipe, a few common restrictions are enumerated via suitableForDiet. The keywords property can also be used to add more detail.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Recipe

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A diet restricted to certain foods or preparations for cultural, religious, health or lifestyle reasons.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RestrictedDiet

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An adjective characterizing the main aspect of a dish.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Characteristic

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Every ingredient is a food which can be used to prepare dishes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Ingredient

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: User is the class which represents the requests of the application user in terms of wanted ingredients, wanted diet, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: User

owl:NamedIndividual.schema:address: Via Carlo Valvassori Peroni, 41, Milano, Italy
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Trattoria Sole Milano
